<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="128" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea brevithorax" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevithorax">Oberea brevithorax</taxonomicName>
was first described as a valid species by Gressitt in 1936 but was downgraded as a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea binotaticollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotaticollis">Oberea binotaticollis</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1915 by Breuning in his revision. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kurihara, T" journalOrPublisher="The Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" pagination="193 - 219" title="Revisional Study on the Genus Oberea Dejean of Taiwan, with Description of Three New Species (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae)." volume="13" year="2007">Kurihara and Ohbayashi (2007)</bibRefCitation>
compared them and confirmed that they were two different species, easily distinguished from each other by different body proportions, antennal lengths, and male genitalia. The species was only recorded in China but recently, some specimens collected in Tonkin, Vietnam, were found in MHNG, and they are a new record to Vietnam.
</paragraph>
